\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Reading strategies for honours - ASLC (27/02/2020)\
\

\f1\b0 \ul Key message\
\ulnone Take systematic notes as you read\
Ask yourself Qs as you read\
- why is this relevant?\
- what will be useful from this?\
- what will I need to revisit to properly understand later?\
Read\
- often\
- with a purpose\
- using the 4S system (see below)\
- why is this interesting? Why is it relevant to my project?\
Write early and write often\
- As in come back to your thesis often\
- Can start with intro and background theory now\
	- That said, they don\'92t have to be final versions now, but making some properly formatted and 	   complete notes that will be useful for later is a good idea\
\

\f0\b Thesis sections\

\f1\b0 \
\ul Intro and lit review\
\ulnone - Justifies project\'92s aims, approach and importance\
- Shows your familiarity with the field\
\
\
\ul Methods\
\ulnone - Justify why you use this approach\
\
\
\ul Discussion\
\ulnone - Explains why your research contributes to the field\
- Why are they expected/unusual/important?\
\
\

\f0\b Research journal (750 w/1.5 pages)
\f1\b0 \ul \
\ulnone - read early and often\
- helps to develop thesis\
- audience is general physics audience (Rose/James S/Stuart S)\
\
\ul Tips\ulc0 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \ulnone - Stay away from really long papers and review articles\
- Goal: think critically about papers you read\
- Don\'92t paraphrase any part of the paper. Your understanding is more important.\
- Read different types of articles\
- Do provide a link to the paper in your submission\
- Can use ASLC turnitin practice site if you want\
\
\
